docs.text: 1989's " major league " was a delightful surprise .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: i didn't expect much of it when i decided to watch it on cable , but it proved to be fresh and funny .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: however , when the appeal of a movie is its freshness , the sequels are virtually guaranteed to be stale .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: that's certainly true of " major league ii " and the most recent entry , " major league : back to the minors . "
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the title is , of course , a contradiction .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: shouldn't it be " minor league ? "
docs.label: negative

docs.text: that contradiction suggests the lengths to which writer/director john warren has gone to squeeze a third movie out of the formula established by the first movie .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: original stars charlie sheen and tom berenger ( who returned for " major league ii " ) are not around , leaving corbin bernsen the only original headliner to make the third movie .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the other veterans who return ( dennis haysbert as voodoo-inspired batter cerrano and takaaki ishibashi as tanaka , who was introduced in " league ii " ) seem to be around just to lend legitimacy to the enterprise .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the only returning cast member who produces any laughs is bob uecker as radio announcer harry doyle , inexplicably broadcasting the games of a minor league team far from his home turf .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the protagonist this time around is retiring pitcher gus cantrell ( scott bakula ) , who is hired by minnesota twins owner roger dorn ( bernsen ) to manage the twins' aaa team , the buzz .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: you can write the movie from here : he finds a group of misfits who need to learn how to play together as a team in order to win .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: there's a future superstar whose ego keeps him from growing ( walton goggins ) , an ex-ballet dancer ( kenneth johnson ) , a broken-down old timer ( thom barry ) , twin outfielders both named juan ( the difilippo triplets ) , and a couple pitchers with throwing problems ( judson mills and peter mackenzie ) .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: along the way , gus picks up cerrano and tanaka ( gus is supposedly an old teammate of theirs , even though he wasn't in either of the preceding films ) .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: sum total : none .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the entire enterprise is artificial , and the cast is not ready for the hollywood majors .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: gus' antagonist is twins manager leonard huff ( ted mcginley ) .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: leonard is a slimy , sniveling little egotist , and the twins are lazy , spoiled , and full of themselves .

docs.text: ( even watching the first movie i wondered why any real-life team would lend itself to being caricatured in this manner ) .

docs.text: " back to the minors " is a movie that has no reason to exist .
